body_html:
Can all the tensorFlow model that's successfully working in a desktop environment also sucessfully working on a mobile application with Tensorflow mobile?

Unfortunately, not always. TensorFlow Mobile only supports a subset of the desktop ops, kernels and types. At the moment, there's no way to know with 100% certainty a priori that your model will run with TensorFlow Mobile short of actually running it. As an example, take a look at the Android ops listing.

body:
> Can all the tensorFlow model that's successfully working in a desktop environment also sucessfully working on a mobile application with Tensorflow mobile?

Unfortunately, not always. TensorFlow Mobile only supports a subset of the desktop ops, kernels and types. At the moment, there's no way to know with 100% certainty a priori that your model will run with TensorFlow Mobile short of actually running it. As an example, take a look at the [Android ops listing](https://cs.corp.google.com/piper///depot/google3/third_party/tensorflow/core/kernels/BUILD?rcl=221644777&l=5241).
